        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2571,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2571,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01AEJLbKaskxxHpzfzF9e8fD\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"helpMe\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Perfect! Let me help you get specific about who you're selling to and what keeps them up at night.\\\",\\n  \\\"template\\\": \\\"**1. Who are they?**\\\\n[Job title/role] at [company size/type] who [specific context about their work]\\\\n\\\\n**2. What's their main problem?**\\\\nThey spend [time/effort] trying to [specific task], which makes them feel [emotion] because [consequence]\\\\n\\\\n**3. What are they actually trying to achieve?**\\\\nThey want to [desired outcome] so they can [bigger goal/impact]\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why haven't they solved this yet?**\\\\nExisting solutions [what they've tried or what's available] but [why it falls short]\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"**1. Who:** Podcast hosts at mid-size shows (50K-500K downloads/month) who are juggling production, editing, and guest booking themselves.\\\\n\\\\n**2. Problem:** They spend 5-10 hours per week manually searching LinkedIn, Twitter, and email lists to find guests, which makes them frustrated because it pulls them away from actually creating content and growing their audience.\\\\n\\\\n**3. Goal:** They want to book high-quality, relevant guests consistently so they can focus on production and grow their listener base without burning out.\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why it hasn't worked:** They've tried asking their network or using generic guest databases, but those either dry up quickly or give them irrelevant matches that waste their time vetting.\\\",\\n    \\\"**1. Who:** Emerging thought leaders and B2B service providers (consultants, coaches, agencies) who want podcast exposure but don't have a systematic way to pitch themselves.\\\\n\\\\n**2. Problem:** They manually pitch to podcasts one-by-one, get rejected most of the time, and feel invisible because they can't get in front of the right audiences.\\\\n\\\\n**3. Goal:** They want to appear on 10-15 relevant podcasts per quarter so they can build credibility and generate leads without spending all their time pitching.\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why it hasn't worked:** Existing podcast directories are outdated, and cold pitching has a 2-5% success rate because hosts get hundreds of pitches they don't have time to read.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3051,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":543,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
