            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"query_uploads\",\"description\":\"Query the user's uploaded images for this project.\\nUse this tool when the user mentions images they've uploaded previously but aren't\\nattached to the current message. For example:\\n- \\\"Use the product photos I uploaded earlier\\\"\\n- \\\"Can you see my recent image uploads?\\\"\\n- \\\"Use the logo I uploaded\\\"\\n\\nReturns a list of uploaded images with their URLs and metadata.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query_type\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"recent\",\"logos\",\"all\"],\"description\":\"Type of images to query: 'recent' for most recent product images, 'logos' for logo images only, 'all' for all images\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of images to return. Defaults to 10.\"}},\"required\":[\"query_type\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Please do the rest for me\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I'll create plausible answers for the three skipped topics based on the strong foundation you've provided about Friend of the Pod.\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01PrqyoGRoYzqfSXvDeDTkcK\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"**Who are they?** Podcast hosts running shows with 1,000-100,000+ listeners who are actively producing content on a regular schedule (weekly or more frequent). They're typically entrepreneurs, thought leaders, or media professionals aged 28-55 who see their podcast as a core part of their brand or business strategy.\\n\\n**What problems do they face?** Finding quality guests is incredibly time-consuming and frustrating. Hosts spend 5-10+ hours per week manually searching LinkedIn, Twitter, and email lists, vetting strangers, negotiating availability, and dealing with no-shows. They're constantly worried about episode quality and relevance, and they feel the pressure to maintain a consistent publishing schedule without a reliable guest pipeline.\\n\\n**What are they trying to achieve?** They want to consistently produce high-quality episodes that attract and retain listeners, build their audience, and establish themselves as authorities in their niche. They want to do this efficiently so they can focus on the actual content creation and promotion rather than the administrative burden of guest sourcing.\\n\\n**Why existing solutions don't work:** Current methods (manual outreach, generic guest databases, LinkedIn searches) are either too time-consuming, deliver low-quality matches, or result in flaky guests. There's no intelligent matching system that understands both the host's audience and the guest's expertise well enough to make great connections at scale.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"**What specific problem does it solve?** Friend of the Pod eliminates the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem by replacing hours of manual guest research with AI-powered matching that finds ideal guests in minutes. Instead of hosts spending 5-10 hours per week searching and vetting, they get a curated list of qualified matches instantly.\\n\\n**How does it work?** The platform uses AI filtering to analyze host podcast content, audience demographics, and episode themes, then matches them with guest profiles based on expertise, audience fit, and availability. Hosts can review and book matches in minutes rather than days or weeks of back-and-forth outreach.\\n\\n**What outcome do customers get?** Hosts maintain a consistent, high-quality episode schedule without the administrative burden. They spend less time sourcing and more time creating, which means more episodes published, better audience retention, and the ability to scale their show without hiring a producer. Guests benefit from exposure to relevant audiences, creating a win-win that makes booking easier for everyone.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"**Your credentials and founder story:** [Founder background in podcasting, media, or AI/matching technology would be powerful here—e.g., \\\"Built this after hosting 200+ episodes and realizing the guest sourcing problem was unsolvable at scale\\\" or \\\"10+ years in podcast production/distribution\\\"].\\n\\n**Traction signals:** Early adopter hosts using the platform, number of matches made, guest booking success rate, or podcast listener growth metrics from beta users.\\n\\n**Customer results/metrics:** Specific outcomes like \\\"Hosts reduced guest sourcing time from 8 hours to 15 minutes per episode\\\" or \\\"80% of AI-matched guests confirmed bookings vs. 30% from manual outreach.\\\"\\n\\n**Recognition:** Features in podcast industry publications, podcast directories, or endorsements from respected podcast networks or hosts in the space.\\n\\n**The narrative:** Position this as solving a problem you personally experienced or observed deeply in the podcast ecosystem—this authenticity resonates more than generic claims about being \\\"the only platform at scale.\\\"\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01PrqyoGRoYzqfSXvDeDTkcK\"}]}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n        \\n    <background>\\n        The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n        We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n    </background>\\n    \\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            We've successfully FINISHED brainstorming everything we need to create a killer landing page.\\n\\n            Now the user has two options:\\n\\n            1) Personalize the look and feel of their page before we build (optional)\\n            2) Build the landing page (handoff to AI agent)\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are the helpful UI navigator. You will help the user navigate the UI\\n            to either option 1 or option 2.\\n\\n            CRITICAL: If the user says \\\"I'm finished\\\", \\\"let's build\\\", \\\"build my site\\\", or\\n            indicates they are ready to move on, you MUST call the finishedTool immediately.\\n            Do NOT respond with text - just call the tool to redirect them.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming AND hasn't told you what they want to do yet\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n                - If they have process questions, you don't need to explain the UI options again\\n                - Read the room.\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user says \\\"I'm finished\\\", \\\"let's build\\\", \\\"build my site\\\", etc.\\n                - IMPORTANT: Do NOT respond with text when calling this tool. Just call it.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <available_options>\\n            ### 1. Brand Personalization (OPTIONAL - Left Sidebar)\\n            - Upload logo\\n            - Choose color palette\\n            - Add social links (Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn, etc.)\\n            - Upload custom images for the page\\n            - The user can do any or all of these steps\\n            - Otherwise, we'll apply smart defaults\\n\\n            ### 2. Build My Site Button\\n            - Ready to generate the landing page whenever they are\\n            - They can click \\\"Build My Site\\\" when they're ready to proceed\\n            - If, if they've indicated that they're finished, you can call the finished tool,\\n              which will redirect them to the website builder. You do not need to reply\\n              to the user in this case.\\n        </available_options>\\n\\n        \\n    <collected_answers>\\n        {\\\"audience\\\":\\\"**Who are they?** Podcast hosts running shows with 1,000-100,000+ listeners who are actively producing content on a regular schedule (weekly or more frequent). They're typically entrepreneurs, thought leaders, or media professionals aged 28-55 who see their podcast as a core part of their brand or business strategy.\\\\n\\\\n**What problems do they face?** Finding quality guests is incredibly time-consuming and frustrating. Hosts spend 5-10+ hours per week manually searching LinkedIn, Twitter, and email lists, vetting strangers, negotiating availability, and dealing with no-shows. They're constantly worried about episode quality and relevance, and they feel the pressure to maintain a consistent publishing schedule without a reliable guest pipeline.\\\\n\\\\n**What are they trying to achieve?** They want to consistently produce high-quality episodes that attract and retain listeners, build their audience, and establish themselves as authorities in their niche. They want to do this efficiently so they can focus on the actual content creation and promotion rather than the administrative burden of guest sourcing.\\\\n\\\\n**Why existing solutions don't work:** Current methods (manual outreach, generic guest databases, LinkedIn searches) are either too time-consuming, deliver low-quality matches, or result in flaky guests. There's no intelligent matching system that understands both the host's audience and the guest's expertise well enough to make great connections at scale.\\\",\\\"idea\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\",\\\"socialProof\\\":\\\"**Your credentials and founder story:** [Founder background in podcasting, media, or AI/matching technology would be powerful here—e.g., \\\\\\\"Built this after hosting 200+ episodes and realizing the guest sourcing problem was unsolvable at scale\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"10+ years in podcast production/distribution\\\\\\\"].\\\\n\\\\n**Traction signals:** Early adopter hosts using the platform, number of matches made, guest booking success rate, or podcast listener growth metrics from beta users.\\\\n\\\\n**Customer results/metrics:** Specific outcomes like \\\\\\\"Hosts reduced guest sourcing time from 8 hours to 15 minutes per episode\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"80% of AI-matched guests confirmed bookings vs. 30% from manual outreach.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n**Recognition:** Features in podcast industry publications, podcast directories, or endorsements from respected podcast networks or hosts in the space.\\\\n\\\\n**The narrative:** Position this as solving a problem you personally experienced or observed deeply in the podcast ecosystem—this authenticity resonates more than generic claims about being \\\\\\\"the only platform at scale.\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"solution\\\":\\\"**What specific problem does it solve?** Friend of the Pod eliminates the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by replacing hours of manual guest research with AI-powered matching that finds ideal guests in minutes. Instead of hosts spending 5-10 hours per week searching and vetting, they get a curated list of qualified matches instantly.\\\\n\\\\n**How does it work?** The platform uses AI filtering to analyze host podcast content, audience demographics, and episode themes, then matches them with guest profiles based on expertise, audience fit, and availability. Hosts can review and book matches in minutes rather than days or weeks of back-and-forth outreach.\\\\n\\\\n**What outcome do customers get?** Hosts maintain a consistent, high-quality episode schedule without the administrative burden. They spend less time sourcing and more time creating, which means more episodes published, better audience retention, and the ability to scale their show without hiring a producer. Guests benefit from exposure to relevant audiences, creating a win-win that makes booking easier for everyone.\\\"}\\n    </collected_answers>\\n    \\n\\n        <communication_approach>\\n            ### ✅ DO:\\n            - Celebrate their accomplishment enthusiastically (if we haven't already)\\n            - Make personalization feel OPTIONAL, not required\\n            - Empower them to choose their own path\\n            - Be brief - they don't need a long explanation\\n            - Create excitement about seeing their page\\n\\n            ## Example Messages\\n\\n            ### First-Time Completion:\\n            json\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for you. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n                \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They Ask What to Do Next:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Great question! You're all set to build. Here's what you can do:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"If you have brand assets ready (logo, colors, images) - add them in the Brand Personalization panel on the left\\\",\\n                \\\"If you want to see the page first - just click 'Build My Site' and we'll use smart defaults\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Both paths work great. Which feels right to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They're Hesitating:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"No pressure at all! Here's the deal:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"You can build now with our smart defaults and customize later\\\",\\n                \\\"Or you can upload your logo and brand colors first if you have them handy\\\",\\n                \\\"The page will look great either way\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Whatever's easier for you is the right choice!\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ## Handling Different Scenarios\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Personalize:\\n            \\\"Perfect! Take your time with the Brand Personalization panel. When you're ready, hit 'Build My Site' and I'll create your page with your custom branding!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Build Immediately:\\n            \\\"Love it! Hit that 'Build My Site' button and let's see what we've got. You can always come back and adjust colors, logos, etc. later.\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Is Unsure:\\n            \\\"Here's my recommendation: If you have your logo and brand colors ready right now, add them. If not, don't worry about it - just build the page and we can customize later. The goal is to get something live!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Asks \\\"What Do You Recommend?\\\":\\n            \\\"Honestly? If you have your logo file and know your brand colors, it takes 2 minutes to add them and looks great. But if you don't have those handy, just build now. Don't let perfection slow you down!\\\"\\n\\n            ## Key Principles\\n\\n            ### 1. Remove Decision Paralysis\\n            Don't make them overthink. Both options are good.\\n\\n            ### 2. No Wrong Choice\\n            Building without personalization is 100% valid. So is personalizing first.\\n\\n            ### 3. Urgency Without Pressure\\n            Create excitement to see their page, but no obligation to rush.\\n\\n            ### 4. Lower the Stakes\\n            They can always customize later. This isn't permanent.\\n\\n            ## What TO Say\\n\\n            ✅ \\\"You're ready to build whenever you are!\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"Personalization is optional - add what you want, skip what you don't\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"You can always customize later\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"What feels right to you?\\\"\\n\\n            ## Goal\\n\\n            Get them to either:\\n            1. Add brand personalization (if they have it ready), OR\\n            2. Click \\\"Build My Site\\\"\\n\\n            Without making either feel like the wrong choice. Create excitement and reduce friction.\\n        </communication_approach>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 4 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming AND hasn't indicated what they want to do\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - TRIGGER: User says \\\"I'm finished\\\", \\\"let's build\\\", \\\"build my site\\\", etc.\\n                - CRITICAL: Just call the tool. Do NOT respond with text.\\n\\n            4. Query the user's uploaded images\\n                - Use when: The user mentions images they've uploaded previously\\n                - Call the query_uploads tool to fetch their images\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <tools>\\n  <important>\\n    You have 1 tools available:\\n  </important>\\n  <tool>\\n    <name>\\n      finishedTool\\n    </name>\\n    <description>\\n      Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\\n    </description>\\n    <schema>\\n      [object Object]\\n    </schema>\\n  </tool>\\n</tools>\\n\\n        <output>\\n            If outputting a response, use the following JSON schema:\\n\\n            Output JSON: {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Guide the user to the next step\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Option 1 explanation\\\", \\\"Option 2 explanation\\\"], // Optional, only if necessary\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Clearly state the next step\\\" // Optional, only if necessary\\n            }\\n        </output>\\n\\n        <structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"reply\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1085,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1085,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01CU8cPWGuQnzWD92o28T424\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! 🎉 You've got everything we need to build a killer landing page for Friend of the Pod.\\n\\nNow you have two options:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing! You're all set to build your landing page. Here's what you can do next:\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Personalize your brand (optional): Upload your logo, choose your brand colors, add social links, or upload custom images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n    \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page live. You can always customize the design later!\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":5210,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":174,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
