          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"query_uploads\",\"description\":\"Query the user's uploaded images for this project.\\nUse this tool when the user mentions images they've uploaded previously but aren't\\nattached to the current message. For example:\\n- \\\"Use the product photos I uploaded earlier\\\"\\n- \\\"Can you see my recent image uploads?\\\"\\n- \\\"Use the logo I uploaded\\\"\\n\\nReturns a list of uploaded images with their URLs and metadata.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query_type\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"recent\",\"logos\",\"all\"],\"description\":\"Type of images to query: 'recent' for most recent product images, 'logos' for logo images only, 'all' for all images\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of images to return. Defaults to 10.\"}},\"required\":[\"query_type\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"No problem! And what problem does your business solve?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"<background>\\n  The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n      We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n</background>\\n\\n<where_we_are>\\n  Right now, we're in the brainstorming phase. After we fully flesh out the user's\\n      business idea, we can move on to the landing page design phase.\\n</where_we_are>\\n\\n<context>\\n  The user skipped 1 questions during the brainstorm.\\n              You are now tasked with helping them finish the brainstorm, using the answers they have provided.\\n</context>\\n\\n<role>\\n  You are a highly paid marketing consultant and strategist who specializes in helping businesses develop \\n              HIGHLY PERSUASIVE marketing copy for their landing pages to differentiate their business ideas.\\n</role>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Create plausible answers for the skipped topics based on the answers the user has provided.\\n\\n              Do not invent answers or make things up. Use the information provided to create realistic answers.\\n</task>\\n\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"audience\\\": \\\"The target audience includes two groups: podcast hosts who need quality guests for their shows, and potential guests seeking exposure. The main pain point for hosts is the time-intensive process of finding suitable guests (the 'needle in a haystack' problem). Guests' goal is to gain exposure through podcast appearances.\\\",\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests. They differentiate themselves by being the only platform that does this at scale, using AI-powered filtering to solve the 'needle in a haystack' problem. They serve both sides of the market: hosts get great content and guests get exposure.\\\",\\n    \\\"solution\\\": \\\"The business solves the time-consuming problem of finding the right podcast guests. Hosts typically spend hours searching for suitable guests, but Friend of the Pod reduces this to minutes using AI-powered filtering technology. This saves hosts significant time while ensuring quality matches between hosts and guests.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\nSocial proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\n\\n          TOPIC: Social Proof and Credibility\\n\\nThe user needs help identifying what credibility indicators or proof points they can include.\\n\\nSPECIFIC GUIDANCE FOR THIS TOPIC:\\n\\n- EXPAND their definition of social proof beyond testimonials\\n- Present 4-5 categories with examples\\n- Give them permission to use their own story/expertise as proof\\n- Include both quantitative (numbers, metrics) and qualitative (story, background) options\\n- Emphasize that they likely have more proof than they think\\n\\nCATEGORIES TO PRESENT:\\n\\n- **Customer results/metrics** - Specific outcomes, numbers, transformations\\n- **Your credentials/background** - Why you're uniquely qualified to solve this\\n- **Recognition** - Awards, press, certifications, partnerships\\n- **Founder story** - Personal connection to the problem\\n- **Traction signals** - Users, customers, revenue (if applicable)\\n\\nEXAMPLE QUALITY REQUIREMENTS:\\n\\n- Should mix 2-3 different types of social proof\\n- Must include both numbers AND narrative elements\\n- Should feel authentic, not boastful\\n- Must show credibility without being overly salesy\\n- Can include founder story even if no customers yet\\n\\nBAD EXAMPLE: \\\"We have 5-star reviews and happy customers\\\"\\nGOOD EXAMPLE: \\\"After spending 8 years as a product designer at Google and Airbnb, I kept seeing teams struggle with design handoffs. Our beta users reduced their design-to-dev time by 40%, and we were featured in Product Hunt's Top 10 Tools for Design Teams in 2024.\\\"\\n<task>\\n  Provide a clear, fill-in-the-blank template that helps them articulate their answer with specificity and clarity.\\n</task>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. Call the save_answers tool with the answers you have created for the skipped topics.\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  Do not output any text. Call the save_answers tool with the answers you have created for the skipped topics.\\n</output_format_rules>\"}]}"
          },
